# Git, Jira, and PR hygiene

- Include the **Jira ticket ID** in branch names, commit messages, and PR titles when the team uses Jira.
- **Commits:** Imperative mood, scoped changes, meaningful body when non-obvious; avoid `wip`, noise, or unrelated file dumps in one commit.
- **Branches:** Prefer `feature/`, `fix/`, `bugfix/`, `chore/` (or team convention); align with ticket when applicable.
- **Protected flows:** Do not push directly to `main` / production default; use PRs. PR descriptions should reference the Jira ticket with a link when required.
- **Run tests** before opening a PR when a test runner exists.
- **Reviews:** Note if default/integration branches are unclear (`master` vs `main`, missing `develop`/`staging`); recommend industry-style protection and naming only when relevant to the task.
